title: 14. Somethin' I'm Good At - Brett Eldredge
text: by Kaysha_Lee Since I heard he was coming out with a new single when he hosted the Today show I few weeks ago and then announced the name by accident, I could not wait to hear it! Absolutely Love it! Need more please! I would add more stars if I could In love. Please come to Lubbock so I can hear this live. WOW by Awesome18069 This is one of best song's I've heard in awhile! It perfectly shows his personality and his goofy side. It is one of those songs you can just blare with the windows down for hours. I highly recommend this song and all his other music Biography Born: March 23, 1986 in Paris, IL Genre: Country Years Active: '10s Singing country music with a soulful edge and more than a dash of pop polish, Brett Eldredge was born in Paris, Illinois on March 23, 1986, and grew up listening to singers Ray Charles, Frank Sinatra, and Bobby Darin. After hearing Brooks & Dunn at the age of 16, he became fascinated by country music, a fascination that stayed with him when he began attending Elmhurst College in Chicago.
